# effect / reader / handler split across a 3-level import chain

Regression for the JS backend (emit-js standalone, whole-program effect
analysis). `labeled` → `sumFrom` (both in `eff-b`) → `query` (in `eff-a`,
imported into `eff-b`) → performs `Box.read`. Per-module effect analysis didn't
see that `query` is effectful when analysing `eff-b`, so `sumFrom`/`labeled`
weren't CPS-lowered and the Free value leaked (`"sum=" + <Free>` →
`"sum=[object Object]"`, or a runtime throw). Whole-program analysis marks the
whole transitive chain effectful.

[sumFrom, labeled](./lib/eff-b.ssc)
[runBox](./lib/eff-a.ssc)

```scalascript
println(runBox(() => sumFrom(0)))
println(runBox(() => labeled(0)))
println(runBox(() => labeled(0) + "!" + sumFrom(0)))
```
